According to the linking rule, when a child returns to hospital within 28 days of discharge, the separate hospital periods are linked together and count cumulatively toward the 12-week limit. Arthur was discharged, stayed home for 2 weeks (14 days), then was readmitted 15 days later - well within the 28-day linking period. Therefore:
- First hospital stay: 10 weeks
- Second hospital stay: 3 weeks  
- **Cumulative total: 13 weeks**

